  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Songming Upland Community Sustainable Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Songming Upland Community Sustainable Development project will provide cattle, pigs or goats to 150 families in three impoverished upland communities of Songming County, Yunnan Province. This project will also support agroecology through chemical-free farming, construction of biogas units, installation of local barns and renovation of kitchens and toilets. Each community will form self-help groups which, among other things, will develop a local waste management system to improve local sanitation and compost utilization. Self-help groups will participate in training on Heifer&#x2019;s Values-Based Holistic Community Development model, which includes the Heifer Cornerstones, group management, Participatory Community Sustainable Development Planning, gender justice, improved animal management, biogas construction, barn renovation, kitchens and toilets, substitution of chemical pesticides and fertilizers and waste management. Project participants will pass on animals, skills and knowledge to another 150 families.</narrative>
  </description>
